  Our Team : American Healthcare Capital











































































Our Team



Executive Team



Jack Eskenazi
Founder & Sr Vice President




jack@ahcteam.com
Jack Eskenazi founded American Healthcare Capital in 1990 and HealthCare Receivable Lenders in 2014 after ending a prosperous real estate career that spanned over twenty five years. He is a graduate of Riverside Military Academy, Ohio State University, and UCLA’s School of Business. He was a pro-bono Adjunct Professor at Cal State Northridge University, teaching from his book “Valuations of Real Estate and Business Opportunities.” Subsequently, the University bestowed an honorary degree for his civic contribution as a Civil Rights Commissioner for the State of California. Today, Jack is active in all aspects of AHC, with a vison to expand its services to other financial services and products.





Jennifer Le
Managing Vice President


										Valuations and Buyside Engagements									

jennifer@ahcteam.com
Jennifer Le joined American HealthCare Capital in 2009. She has a B.S. degree from the University of California, Irvine. As Managing Vice President, Jennifer oversees all staff and operations. She is also involved in sales and marketing of all listings. During her tenure at AHC, she has gained an expertise in valuation of all types of healthcare businesses, large and small. She has represented both buyers and sellers in hundreds of transactions. 





Stephanie Carton
General Manager & Vice President


										Administrative Services									

										Valuations and Buyside Engagements									

stephanie@ahcteam.com
Stephanie Carton inaugurated her career shortly after attending Baruch College – Zicklin School of Business. Her skill sets are in the implementation of management systems, in concert with marketing philosophies and objectives. Mrs. Carton has international experience and is fluent in French and Spanish, serving as AHC’s bridge between our international buyers and sellers. She and her staff preserve transparency to maintain total clarity, minimizing any possible risks for oversights. 



Vice Presidents




Mike Moran


										Behavioral Health & I/DD									

										Home Health, Wound Care, and LTC									

mmoran@ahcteam.com
Mike Moran, our Executive Vice President, comes from the world of niche investment companies, in which he gained M&A experience in hospitality, software, and real estate. He has a B.S. in Finance and Psychology from Syracuse University. Mike has been a key team member since 2015 and has closed a number of transactions in Behavioral Health, I/DD, Home Health, Medical Staffing, and Long Term Care. He also has a strong footprint within Wound Care and other emerging modalities. Mike is Senior Loan Officer at our financing subsidiary, Healthcare Receivable Lenders, and remains one of our top producing M&A advisors. 







Andre Ulloa


										Pharmacy									

										Home Health/Hospice									

andre@ahcteam.com
Andre Ulloa specializes in Pharmacy and Home Health/Hospice. He also works in Urgent Care/Clinics and Dermatology. He graduated with a B.A. degree from the University of California, Los Angeles, and is bilingual in English and Spanish. Along with sell-side and buy-side representation, Andre can assist clients with debt financing. Prior to joining American HealthCare Capital, he was a Principal at an investment bank. As an agent of a registered broker-dealer, he was helping lower middle market clients with financial transactions including capital raises, debt restructurings, and sell-side and buy-side acquisition projects. 







Kirk Bodaghi


										Hospice									

										Clinics									

kirk@ahcteam.com
Kirk Bodaghi joined American HealthCare Capital in 2010. As a Vice President, he works with both buyers and sellers to close transactions, specializing in hospice and clinic deals. Prior to joining American Healthcare Capital, Kirk worked in Strategic Business Development and Marketing at several companies, and served in staff positions in medical start up technology firms. He holds a Bachelor’s Degree from the University of California Berkeley. He is available for consultation on transactions of any size, large or small. 







Alan Hymowitz


										Pharmacy									

										Home Infusion									

alan@ahcteam.com
Alan Hymowitz specializes in all types of Pharmacy and Home Health Care. He has more than 25 years of extensive experience in home infusion, specialty pharmacy, and home health care, both as an owner and manager. With his past successes in business development, due diligence analysis, managing turnaround projects, and as an owner, Alan is highly qualified in the valuation process for mergers and acquisitions. Prior to AHC, he worked for several large regional and national companies. He served on the Los Angeles Home Care Council as Vice President and President for almost 10 years.







Irwin Frank


