Michael Bass


										DME, O&P, and PT									

										Diagnostics									

michael@ahcteam.com
Michael Bass, MBA, CPA has over 25 years of Mergers & Acquisitions experience in healthcare. He was an officer for a national public Orthotic & Prosthetic company that acquired many facilities. Following the sale of this company to a larger public national O&P company, Michael represented O&P companies in sales, and also developed strong experience representing Outpatient Rehabilitation and other types of Therapy Services companies. He has a strong network of national and regional corporate buyers in O&P and Physical Therapy, as well as Private Equity Groups focusing on healthcare services.







Dr. Michael Murphy


										Medical Director									

										Long Term Care									

michael.murphy@ahcteam.com
Dr. Michael A. Murphy serves as Vice President and Medical Director at AHC providing transaction advisory services to payers, providers and healthcare technology companies on the buy side and sell side. He brings years of experience as a HealthCare consultant with several large national companies. Dr. Murphy also served as a Research Fellow at the Middlesex and University College Medical School, Oxford University and University of California, San Diego, where he conducted primary research in mitochondrial degenerative, muscular, neurological and psychiatric diseases. He practiced medicine following completion of his medical school education at Trinity College, Dublin and later obtained a Masters in Sciences in Neurochemistry from The Institute of Psychiatry, Kings College, London.







David Feuer


										Long Term Care Pharmacy									

