Sara Medley


										Generalist									

sara@ahcteam.com
Sara Medley specializes in consultation, strategic business development, and exit planning for all types of healthcare companies. Prior to joining AHC, she was one of the lead Mergers and Acquisition Advisors at a worldwide Business Brokerage firm in which she successfully negotiated and closed several multi-million dollar transactions. Additionally, she has over 20 years of experience in the Real Estate industry, working with Sellers, Buyers, Investors, PEGS and REIT's in the Residential, Commercial and Business areas. 



Of Counsel




John Rivas


											National HealthCare Attorney & Consultant										

john@ahcteam.com
John J. Rivas provides legal representation to clients in the areas of health care transactions, Stark and Antikickback issues, Medicare/Medicaid Overpayment cases, and Medicaid/Medicare fraud matters. In addition to state court, he is also admitted to practice before the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Texas. John's practice includes the representation of licensed health professionals and entities in practice and business matters, as well as their representation and defense before their respective state licensure and peer review boards. John is a member of the Texas Association of Home Care and the American Health Lawyers Association. His degrees include Juris Doctor, 1993, Texas Tech University School of Law and B.A. in English, 1989, University of Texas at Austin. Bar Admissions: Texas, 1993; New York, 2013; U.S. District Court Western District of Texas.

















 



