↵

The impact of the venture capital industry is hard to ignore. Venture capital–funded information technology companies such
                              as Google, Microsoft, Apple, Intel, and eBay have transformed the U.S. and global economies. Some of the more innovative recent
                              technologies in the health sector have been financed by venture capital, from home glucose self-monitoring devices to drugs
                              such as trastuzumab (Herceptin). See additional examples in Platzer, “Patient Capital.”
                           
